# Books HTML — fidelity & delivery

Read **`application/agent/FIDELITY-RULES.md`** before render, translate, or assemble.

## Per-page (`output/<lang>/page_*.html`)

- Visual PDF order; run-in headings; `page_chrome` header/footer
- Diagrams: PNG `src="../assets/images/…"` + `width` + `height` (never glue dimensions into filename)
- Shell: `main.book-page--sheet` + `article.sheet-flow.prose-page`
- CSS: `prose-page.css` + `code-page.css` / `figures-page.css` as needed

## Assembled (`output/book.html`, `book.vi.html`)

- Same A4 shell per sheet (Rule 8)
- Asset prefix **`assets/`** not `../assets/` (assemble rewrites automatically)
- Must link `prose-page.css`, `code-page.css`, `figures-page.css`

## Mandatory pipeline (every book, every lang)

```bash
PY=application/.venv/bin/python3
$PY application/backend/scripts/extract_pdf_figures.py books/<slug>
$PY application/backend/scripts/upgrade_figure_html.py books/<slug>
$PY application/backend/scripts/refresh_figure_images.py books/<slug>
$PY application/backend/scripts/fix_book_layout.py books/<slug>
$PY application/backend/scripts/validate_page_fidelity.py books/<slug> --lang all
books-cli assemble --book books/<slug> --lang <lang> --output book.<lang>.html
$PY application/backend/scripts/validate_page_fidelity.py books/<slug> --lang all
```

Do not ship if validator fails.
